        Have we been noticing certain inaccuracies recently...?

        Godzilla1995 spotted that I'm Still Standing shows a peak of #34, whereas it made #4 in 1983. (I, too, am that old. LOL) Similarly, Everybody Wants To Rule The World made #2 in 1985, but its recent run shows it as peaking at #86, which is nonsense. Seems like OCC can't handle certain decades-old hits that resurface after years out of the chart. (... Running Up That Hill didn't seem to confuse them.)

        But have a look at #77..... the eternal Mr Brightside had cracked 365 weeks (not days) in the chart last week, but now suddenly it's showing as ***713*** weeks - where did that magically spring from??

        The problem with factual errors from a "trusted source" means that the entire chart is now devalued. :D
